# Dating App Behavior Analysis

This project explores user behavior on a fictional dating app using synthetic data from a Kaggle notebook. The goal is to uncover behavioral
patterns and insights that may contribute to match success. This dataset provides a synthetic representation of user behavior on a fictional dating app

## 📊 Summary

- Explored correlations between income, swiping behavior, and match outcomes.
- Found that higher income users were more active and had more success.
- Optimistic swipe behavior (swiping right more often) led to higher mutual matches.

## 🔍 Key Findings

- Income and engagement are positively correlated.
- Swiping patterns affect match success rate.
- Potential for predictive modeling on user behavior.

## 📌 Next Steps

- Hyperparameter tuning for model accuracy.
- Behavioral analysis over time (e.g., time-of-day usage).
- Analyzing effect of interests/hobbies on matches.

